WEBVTT

00:00.542 --> 00:02.711
- Previously on
"Superman & Lois"...

00:02.752 --> 00:05.422
- That thing Dad was fighting,
how could he beat that?

00:05.463 --> 00:06.089
- He'll beat it.

00:06.131 --> 00:07.924
- I'm just not ready to do
all this without him.

00:07.966 --> 00:09.134
- There's nothing
in this universe

00:09.175 --> 00:10.468
that can stop Superman.

00:10.510 --> 00:11.594
- There might be now.

00:11.636 --> 00:14.597
[dramatic music]

00:14.639 --> 00:19.269
♪ ♪

00:19.310 --> 00:20.687
They purchased it through
Eckworth Industries

00:20.729 --> 00:22.230
to avoid any questions.

00:22.272 --> 00:23.982
- It's got the perfect view.

00:24.024 --> 00:25.817
- Daddy,
he's coming after me.

00:25.859 --> 00:27.986
He wants to destroy my life
and everybody in it.

00:28.028 --> 00:29.696
♪ ♪

00:29.738 --> 00:31.614
- We have to do something.
- We can't, honey.

00:31.656 --> 00:32.907
- I can.

00:32.949 --> 00:34.492
- Jordan, you stay away
from him.

00:34.534 --> 00:35.702
- Lois Lane showed up
with that kid

00:35.744 --> 00:37.370
people been calling Superboy.

00:37.412 --> 00:38.788
- [groans]

00:38.830 --> 00:40.790
- He's got powers?

00:40.832 --> 00:41.791
- It's coming back.

00:41.833 --> 00:44.210
- [roars]

00:44.252 --> 00:45.545
[growls]

00:45.587 --> 00:47.380
- Mom, is he okay?

00:47.422 --> 00:49.758
Mom, is he okay?
- [gasps]

00:49.799 --> 00:51.676
This wasn't supposed to happen.

00:51.718 --> 00:55.764
♪ ♪

00:59.559 --> 01:01.519
- Good night, Chuck.
- Good night, Aidy.

01:01.561 --> 01:04.272
[whooshing overhead]

01:09.152 --> 01:11.571
- [growling]

01:11.613 --> 01:14.574
[tense music]

01:14.616 --> 01:21.539
♪ ♪

01:21.581 --> 01:24.709
[roars]

01:27.754 --> 01:31.674
- [crying]
No. No, no, no, no.

01:31.716 --> 01:34.511
This wasn't supposed to happen.

01:34.552 --> 01:36.513
- Mom.
Mom, is he okay?

01:36.554 --> 01:38.973
[Lois sobs]
- Mom, is he okay?

01:41.184 --> 01:42.727
[tires screech]

01:42.769 --> 01:49.859
♪ ♪

01:50.068 --> 01:53.321
[somber music]

01:53.363 --> 01:56.950
♪ ♪

01:56.991 --> 01:59.911
- Mom, Mom.

01:59.953 --> 02:03.164
- Everyone, stop.

02:03.206 --> 02:07.877
Superman is Lois's friend,
her good friend.

02:07.919 --> 02:09.254
Just--

02:09.295 --> 02:12.590
Give her some space.
Come on.

02:12.632 --> 02:15.135
Timmy, let's go.

02:15.176 --> 02:22.183
♪ ♪

02:25.061 --> 02:26.729
- Jordan.

02:26.771 --> 02:28.857
Jordan, take your father
to the Fortress,

02:28.898 --> 02:30.275
get him to his mother.

02:30.316 --> 02:32.610
Go now.

02:32.652 --> 02:38.741
♪ ♪

02:38.783 --> 02:41.744
- [crying]

02:41.786 --> 02:47.000
♪ ♪

02:47.041 --> 02:48.877
- Grandma!
Grandma!

02:48.918 --> 02:50.628
- Jordan?
- Grandma, please.

02:50.670 --> 02:52.547
You have to help.
- What happened?

02:52.589 --> 02:55.341
- It doesn't matter.
You have to save him.

02:55.383 --> 02:58.428
[dramatic music]

02:58.469 --> 03:05.560
♪ ♪

03:10.899 --> 03:13.151
- He is without a heart.

03:13.193 --> 03:15.111
- His body can heal itself.

03:15.153 --> 03:17.780
- It cannot create new organs.
- Then I'll fly him to the sun.

03:17.822 --> 03:20.450
- That won't help.
- Then what will?

03:20.491 --> 03:22.869
- I don't know.

03:24.078 --> 03:26.789
- Look, I don't care
what you have to do

03:26.831 --> 03:29.667
or what Kryptonian technology
you have to use.

03:31.085 --> 03:33.171
You have to save my dad.

03:34.756 --> 03:37.383
- I'll do all I can.

03:37.425 --> 03:44.515
♪ ♪

03:54.943 --> 03:57.904
[soft dramatic music]

03:57.946 --> 04:04.702
♪ ♪

04:04.744 --> 04:07.705
[vehicle approaching]

04:07.747 --> 04:11.084
♪ ♪

04:11.125 --> 04:14.379
[car doors open, close]

04:43.741 --> 04:48.288
- Where did that thing
even come from?

04:48.329 --> 04:50.665
- Lex Luthor.

04:50.707 --> 04:53.126
- Lex Luthor?
Are you sure?

04:53.167 --> 04:57.338
- He blames me
for putting him in prison.

04:57.380 --> 05:00.425
Once he was released,
he came here and threatened me,

05:00.466 --> 05:02.927
and then he kidnapped my dad
and tried to kill him.

05:02.969 --> 05:05.346
- My God, is Sam okay?

05:05.388 --> 05:07.849
- He's recovering at the DOD.

05:07.890 --> 05:10.810
- I knew that you and Clark
had history with Luthor,

05:10.852 --> 05:13.938
but I didn't realize
it was this bad.

05:13.980 --> 05:16.941
- He warned me, Lana.

05:16.983 --> 05:19.694
He warned me that if I didn't
retire from journalism,

05:19.736 --> 05:20.945
he would come after me.

05:20.987 --> 05:22.989
I should have just stopped.

05:23.031 --> 05:25.783
- No, don't even go there.
- I could have prevented this.

05:25.825 --> 05:27.160
- This isn't your fault.

05:27.201 --> 05:29.704
- I just don't know
what to do.

05:29.746 --> 05:32.749
Luthor's not going to stop
until he destroys my life.

05:32.790 --> 05:35.960
He even moved here
to make sure.

05:36.002 --> 05:38.254
- What do you mean
he moved here?

05:38.296 --> 05:39.839
- Into the Pomono Hotel,

05:39.881 --> 05:42.091
right across the street
from the "Gazette."

05:42.133 --> 05:44.177
- That was his company?

05:44.218 --> 05:46.387
That building
is a historic landmark,

05:46.429 --> 05:48.389
so I had to authorize
that sale.

05:48.431 --> 05:50.183
I had no idea
it was Luthor.

05:50.224 --> 05:52.185
- I'm sure he used
a shell company.

05:52.226 --> 05:54.395
He has dozens
that are virtually impossible

05:54.437 --> 05:56.397
to trace back to him.

05:56.439 --> 05:59.567
- [sighs] Maybe there's a way
to stop the sale.

05:59.609 --> 06:02.862
- No, I will not let you put
yourself in danger like that.

06:02.904 --> 06:05.073
- Well, I'm not going to let
this maniac come to Smallville

06:05.114 --> 06:06.574
and do whatever he wants.

06:06.616 --> 06:08.785
He hurt you.
He hurt your dad.

06:08.826 --> 06:10.620
He could--

06:10.661 --> 06:12.997
♪ ♪

06:13.039 --> 06:15.458
I have to do something.

06:16.834 --> 06:20.213
- Lana, if you get involved
with Luthor,

06:20.254 --> 06:22.632
he is going to come
after you and your family

06:22.673 --> 06:24.342
like he's coming after mine.

06:24.384 --> 06:28.054
Please promise me
you will stay away from him.

06:28.096 --> 06:30.640
♪ ♪

06:30.681 --> 06:32.100
- I'm really worried.

06:32.141 --> 06:34.102
- Jordan told me
about the Fortress.

06:34.143 --> 06:36.437
I feel like if there's anyplace
that could help your dad--

06:36.479 --> 06:38.356
- I guess
it's possible, but...

06:38.398 --> 06:40.900
- But?

06:42.860 --> 06:46.364
- I don't know if my mom and
Jordan can recover from this.

06:46.406 --> 06:49.450
- Jon, I don't know much,
but what I do know

06:49.492 --> 06:51.452
is that your family
can get through anything.

06:51.494 --> 06:53.204
I've seen it,
especially your mom.

06:53.246 --> 06:55.498
- Yeah, but she still hasn't
finished her radiation.

06:55.540 --> 06:58.126
And--and then there's
her reconstruction surgery.

06:58.167 --> 07:00.169
And to lose my dad
with all that still going on,

07:00.211 --> 07:01.921
I mean, it's too much.

07:01.963 --> 07:03.423
- Okay, you just have to take
it one step at a time.

07:03.464 --> 07:05.007
And Jordan--
it's like the second he got

07:05.049 --> 07:07.051
those goggles and that jacket
from Grandpa,

07:07.093 --> 07:09.262
he's been pretending
to be a superhero.

07:09.303 --> 07:10.930
But he's just not ready.
- Okay, he'll figure it out.

07:10.972 --> 07:13.516
He'll figure it out.
There's still time.

07:13.558 --> 07:17.353
- Without my dad,
I'm not sure there is.

07:17.395 --> 07:22.066
[whooshing]

07:22.108 --> 07:25.278
[sighs]
Jordan's back.

07:25.319 --> 07:28.281
- She placed him in an
"altered state of existence."

07:28.322 --> 07:31.367
- What does that mean?

07:31.409 --> 07:34.162
- It's how the Kryptonians
rehabilitate their criminals--

07:34.203 --> 07:38.124
by placing them
into suspended animation.

07:38.166 --> 07:40.710
It's how Dad got to Earth
in his pod.

07:40.751 --> 07:45.298
- Did your grandmother
say anything else?

07:45.339 --> 07:49.093
- Just that she'd do everything
she could for him.

07:49.135 --> 07:51.387
- Thank you.

07:51.429 --> 07:57.643
♪ ♪

07:57.685 --> 08:00.396
- You need to tell me
what is going on here.

08:00.438 --> 08:02.523
I thought when Superman
was taken care of

08:02.565 --> 08:05.735
that you were going to return
to Metropolis.

08:05.776 --> 08:08.905
- I never said that.

08:08.946 --> 08:12.366
- Bash is chomping at the bit
to expand.

08:12.408 --> 08:16.829
You need to at least come in
and hear what he is proposing.

08:16.871 --> 08:18.289
- [sighs]

08:18.331 --> 08:20.416
- This is not like you.

08:20.458 --> 08:22.376
You are letting
your emotions drive you.

08:22.418 --> 08:24.128
- I know what I'm doing.

08:24.170 --> 08:25.963
- Do you even know what
the endgame looks like here?

08:26.005 --> 08:29.091
What else are you trying
to prove, Lex?

08:31.928 --> 08:35.765
Lex.
- That's enough.

08:35.806 --> 08:39.810
Superman is dead.

08:39.852 --> 08:43.314
Can we please
just enjoy the moment?

08:43.356 --> 08:50.321
♪ ♪

08:50.363 --> 08:53.783
- To a brave new world.

08:53.824 --> 08:55.785
- Our world.

08:55.826 --> 09:02.500
♪ ♪

09:05.795 --> 09:10.049
Set up a meeting
with Bash for tomorrow.

09:10.091 --> 09:11.717
- Okay.

09:11.759 --> 09:15.054
♪ ♪

09:15.096 --> 09:17.765
[whooshing]

09:20.851 --> 09:22.770
- [pants]

09:22.812 --> 09:26.816
- Where were you?

09:26.857 --> 09:28.859
- It's not important.

09:28.901 --> 09:33.573
- You didn't tell Mom
everything earlier.

09:33.614 --> 09:35.324
What are you hiding?

09:35.366 --> 09:37.994
At least just tell me
what you were doing.

09:38.035 --> 09:40.121
- I was trying to track
that thing.

09:40.162 --> 09:43.499
- The thing
that killed Dad?

09:43.541 --> 09:45.543
Dude, you can't fight it.

09:45.585 --> 09:47.670
- I know.

09:47.712 --> 09:50.923
- Then why are you
looking for it?

09:50.965 --> 09:52.675
- To get Dad's heart back.

09:52.717 --> 09:54.885
Grandmom said that we might be
able to bring Dad back

09:54.927 --> 09:56.721
if we can get his heart.

09:56.762 --> 10:00.224
- Wait, "might be able to"?

10:00.266 --> 10:02.226
- You're going to have
to trust me.

10:02.268 --> 10:03.894
It's going to work.

10:03.936 --> 10:06.272
This is how we save Dad.

10:11.193 --> 10:12.570
- I think we should tell Mom.

10:12.612 --> 10:14.447
- Mom will be too worried
I'll get hurt.

10:14.488 --> 10:16.782
She'll just try and stop me.
- I'm worried you'll get hurt.

10:16.824 --> 10:18.159
- Do you want
to save Dad or not?

10:18.200 --> 10:20.036
- Of course I do.

10:20.077 --> 10:22.413
- Then trust me.
I can do this.

10:22.455 --> 10:24.999
- How do you know that that
thing even has Dad's heart?

10:25.041 --> 10:28.210
Doesn't it just do
what Luthor tells it?

10:28.252 --> 10:29.587
- You're right.

10:29.629 --> 10:31.339
- Great.
So we can tell Mom.

10:31.380 --> 10:33.549
- I meant about the heart.

10:33.591 --> 10:35.676
That thing probably gave it
to Luthor.

10:35.718 --> 10:37.595
- Okay, well, you can't just
go after that guy.

10:37.637 --> 10:39.430
I mean, he's a total psycho.

10:39.472 --> 10:40.973
- And I have powers.

10:41.015 --> 10:43.517
I'm pretty sure powers
beats psycho every time.

10:43.559 --> 10:45.227
Besides, going after Luthor
is a lot safer

10:45.269 --> 10:47.688
than chasing that thing,
anyway.

10:47.730 --> 10:50.399
- I'm headed
to the "Gazette."

10:50.441 --> 10:52.693
- Today?

10:52.735 --> 10:54.862
- It's my job.
I need to go in.

10:54.904 --> 10:57.615
- Well, but can't Chrissy
handle it?

10:57.657 --> 10:59.283
I mean, with all
that's happened...

10:59.325 --> 11:01.077
- I know, but I--
[sighs]

11:01.118 --> 11:03.496
I can't just sit around here
all day and do nothing.

11:03.537 --> 11:06.832
I can't.
It'll only make me feel worse.

11:06.874 --> 11:09.543
- Are you going to write
about Dad?

11:09.585 --> 11:11.462
- It's going to come out
eventually.

11:11.504 --> 11:13.839
I should be the one
who writes his story.

11:13.881 --> 11:15.257
- Maybe just wait
a little longer.

11:15.299 --> 11:16.842
I mean, there's still a chance.

11:16.884 --> 11:18.511
- I want your dad back,
too, okay?

11:18.552 --> 11:21.222
More than anything.

11:21.263 --> 11:25.768
But this is something
that even Superman...

11:25.810 --> 11:28.020
most likely
cannot recover from.

11:28.062 --> 11:30.606
[dramatic music]

11:30.648 --> 11:32.400
♪ ♪

11:32.441 --> 11:33.984
- You're right.

11:34.026 --> 11:37.863
♪ ♪

11:37.905 --> 11:39.865
- I know
this is hard, okay?

11:39.907 --> 11:42.034
But we have to face the truth.

11:42.076 --> 11:45.830
And I'm here
if you want to talk, okay?

11:45.871 --> 11:49.125
♪ ♪

11:49.166 --> 11:51.752
Text me if you want anything
from Vicky May's.

11:51.794 --> 11:53.671
Love you.

11:53.713 --> 11:56.716
♪ ♪

11:56.757 --> 11:58.259
- Why didn't you say
anything?

11:58.300 --> 12:00.010
- You can't let her
publish that article.

12:00.052 --> 12:01.429
- Jordan--

12:01.470 --> 12:02.763
- Look, just distract her
or something.

12:02.805 --> 12:04.140
I've got this.

12:04.181 --> 12:06.767
♪ ♪

12:06.809 --> 12:08.144
- [sighs]

12:08.185 --> 12:11.981
Mom, hold up.
I'll ride with you.

12:12.022 --> 12:16.193
♪ ♪

12:21.907 --> 12:24.160
- What's all this?

12:24.201 --> 12:25.786
- I'm just going over
the sales agreement

12:25.828 --> 12:27.663
for the Pomono Hotel.

12:27.705 --> 12:29.331
Lex Luthor just bought it.

12:29.373 --> 12:33.210
- Seriously? Who the hell
signed off on that?

12:33.252 --> 12:36.338
- I did.

12:36.380 --> 12:38.758
It was purchased
under a shell corporation--

12:38.799 --> 12:40.718
Eckworth Industries.

12:40.760 --> 12:43.679
The worst part is
he's living there now.

12:43.721 --> 12:45.222
- But why?
The Pomono's a dump.

12:45.264 --> 12:46.724
- Well, he wanted to be close
to the "Gazette"

12:46.766 --> 12:48.726
so he could terrorize Lois.

12:48.768 --> 12:50.603
- You can't let him do that.

12:50.644 --> 12:53.481
- It's not that simple.
- You're the mayor.

12:53.522 --> 12:55.733
Whatever you sign,
just un-sign it.

12:55.775 --> 12:57.234
- If I did that,

12:57.276 --> 13:00.029
I would be making our family
his next target.

13:00.070 --> 13:01.822
- Well, then what can we do?

13:01.864 --> 13:04.825
I mean, we can't sit by
and do nothing.

13:04.867 --> 13:06.368
Mom, I'm serious.

13:06.410 --> 13:08.913
Jon is really worried
about his family.

13:08.954 --> 13:10.623
They're not ready
for Mr. Kent to be gone.

13:10.664 --> 13:12.917
We have to help
keep them safe.

13:12.958 --> 13:16.003
- I understand.

13:16.045 --> 13:19.423
But if Superman
can't stop Lex Luthor,

13:19.465 --> 13:21.050
how can we?

13:21.091 --> 13:23.010
- [sighs]

13:23.052 --> 13:25.638
- I'm listening.

13:25.679 --> 13:27.598
- The board's concerned.

13:27.640 --> 13:30.059
Our stock price
has plummeted 20%

13:30.100 --> 13:31.811
since you got out of prison.

13:31.852 --> 13:33.562
- Then make it go up.

13:33.604 --> 13:35.564
- To do that,
we need your help.

13:35.606 --> 13:39.026
- Cut to the chase, Bash.

13:39.068 --> 13:42.655
- We now live in a world
where CEOs are celebrities.

13:42.696 --> 13:45.991
So we expand
our Metropolis office,

13:46.033 --> 13:47.785
hold a televised
press conference.

13:47.827 --> 13:49.620
It could be
the perfect way for you

13:49.662 --> 13:52.832
to announce your vision
for the future of LuthorCorp.

13:52.873 --> 13:55.167
- My vision...

13:55.209 --> 13:57.086
involves me
staying here.

13:57.127 --> 13:59.004
- In Smallville?

13:59.046 --> 14:02.258
♪ ♪

14:02.299 --> 14:04.635
- Anything else?

14:04.677 --> 14:08.889
♪ ♪

14:08.931 --> 14:10.891
- Janet Olsen
from the "Daily Planet"

14:10.933 --> 14:12.685
wants to do an exposé.

14:12.726 --> 14:15.312
Can we at least set you up
with our social-media team?

14:17.815 --> 14:21.026
- You're going to give me
Superman's heart.

14:21.068 --> 14:22.611
- Are you nuts?

14:22.653 --> 14:23.988
Jordan is going
after Lex Luthor

14:24.029 --> 14:26.490
to get your father's heart?
- Shh.

14:26.532 --> 14:28.284
- Sorry, but my mom
was just lecturing me

14:28.325 --> 14:30.286
about how scary
that man is.

14:30.327 --> 14:32.913
- Okay, well, I'm sure
Jordan can handle him.

14:32.955 --> 14:36.125
- Really? What about
what you said last night?

14:36.166 --> 14:38.502
You literally said
he wasn't ready.

14:38.544 --> 14:40.129
- This is the only way
we can save my dad.

14:40.170 --> 14:41.922
- I want to save
your dad, too,

14:41.964 --> 14:43.924
but going after Luthor
is really dangerous,

14:43.966 --> 14:46.510
and Jordan could get
seriously hurt.

14:46.552 --> 14:48.888
I mean...
[sighs]

14:48.929 --> 14:53.058
Okay, just promise me
you'll talk to your mom.

14:53.100 --> 14:54.393
Okay?

14:56.854 --> 14:59.231
- Where is it?

14:59.273 --> 15:01.108
- Not here.

15:01.150 --> 15:04.111
♪ ♪

15:04.153 --> 15:07.990
- I want it back!

15:08.032 --> 15:09.992
- Or what?

15:10.034 --> 15:13.495
You're going to kill me,
in front of all these people?

15:13.537 --> 15:19.335
♪ ♪

15:19.376 --> 15:22.379
You're not ready
for this.

15:22.421 --> 15:28.802
♪ ♪

15:28.844 --> 15:33.682
When you make an enemy,
you have to commit.

15:33.724 --> 15:38.270
So next time
you come after me...

15:38.312 --> 15:41.273
you better be ready
to kill me.

15:41.315 --> 15:48.280
♪ ♪

15:48.322 --> 15:50.491
- Damn.

15:50.532 --> 15:53.118
- We're done here.

15:56.580 --> 15:59.625
[door bells jingling,
door clicks]

16:01.835 --> 16:04.046
- Mom, wait, wait, wait.

16:04.088 --> 16:05.589
What you doing?

16:05.631 --> 16:08.509
- What I have to do.

16:08.550 --> 16:10.844
Superman is dead.
The world needs to know.

16:10.886 --> 16:12.680
- Okay, sure,
but w-what if he's not?

16:12.721 --> 16:14.223
- Honey, we have talked
about this.

16:14.264 --> 16:16.141
- No, you don't understand.

16:16.183 --> 16:17.810
There's something
I need to tell you.

16:17.851 --> 16:19.979
Um...
- Luthor.

16:20.020 --> 16:22.982
♪ ♪

16:23.023 --> 16:25.317
- Mom, Mom, wait.

16:25.359 --> 16:27.152
- Jonathan, let me go.

16:27.194 --> 16:34.243
♪ ♪

16:35.452 --> 16:37.037
I know what you did.

16:37.079 --> 16:39.248
- You look rattled, Lois.

16:39.289 --> 16:41.542
- Mom, let's just go.

16:41.583 --> 16:44.003
- You should listen
to the boy.

16:44.044 --> 16:46.171
- You're mad
I took 17 years?

16:46.213 --> 16:49.383
I am going to take
the rest of your life.

16:49.425 --> 16:51.635
- That's the second time today
someone from your family

16:51.677 --> 16:53.554
has threatened my life.

16:53.595 --> 16:55.055
- What are you
talking about?

16:55.097 --> 16:58.559
- [softly]
Jordan.

16:58.600 --> 17:01.270
- Playing dress up...

17:01.311 --> 17:03.647
like his dad...

17:03.689 --> 17:05.774
Superman.

17:05.816 --> 17:08.193
- You're wrong.

17:08.235 --> 17:11.447
- Enough of your lies.

17:11.488 --> 17:15.325
Should have known
you were married to Superman.

17:15.367 --> 17:18.287
- That's why
you went after me...

17:18.328 --> 17:20.581
to protect your husband.

17:20.622 --> 17:24.293
[sighs]

17:24.334 --> 17:26.420
Do you have powers, too?

17:26.462 --> 17:30.340
♪ ♪

17:30.382 --> 17:32.718
Probably for the best.

17:32.760 --> 17:34.970
It's a dangerous business
being a superhero.

17:35.012 --> 17:36.972
- You leave my boys
out of this.

17:37.014 --> 17:40.559
♪ ♪

17:40.601 --> 17:43.437
- You didn't leave
my daughter out of it.

17:43.479 --> 17:45.189
My daughter
lost her father.

17:45.230 --> 17:47.816
That is why kids
are on the table.

17:47.858 --> 17:50.402
And if you or your sons
ever set foot

17:50.444 --> 17:53.280
on my property again...

17:53.322 --> 17:56.158
you won't walk out.

17:56.200 --> 17:59.703
♪ ♪

17:59.745 --> 18:02.122
- Mom...

18:02.164 --> 18:04.708
Mom, come on.

18:04.750 --> 18:07.086
Let's go.

18:07.127 --> 18:11.173
♪ ♪

18:19.181 --> 18:20.724
- These are
all the property sales

18:20.766 --> 18:22.142
from the past six months?

18:22.184 --> 18:23.769
- Yeah.

18:23.811 --> 18:25.354
The Pomono Hotel,
Chandler's Field,

18:25.395 --> 18:27.231
and the old Sullivan Farm.

18:27.272 --> 18:31.193
- And we're sure the other two
aren't secretly Lex Luthor?

18:31.235 --> 18:32.778
- Not as far
as I can tell.

18:32.820 --> 18:34.571
- Okay, well, we need
to be absolutely sure,

18:34.613 --> 18:36.740
because this man
has shell corporations

18:36.782 --> 18:39.243
for his shell corporations.

18:39.284 --> 18:42.162
- Is it really
that big of a deal?

18:42.204 --> 18:44.248
The Pomono is a money pit.

18:44.289 --> 18:47.501
- I already let one billionaire
try to destroy our town.

18:47.543 --> 18:49.795
- No offense, Lana,

18:49.837 --> 18:53.549
but this town
needs investors.

18:53.590 --> 18:56.552
- Do you know
how many mom-and-pop shops

18:56.593 --> 18:59.930
LuthorCorp has put
out of business?

18:59.972 --> 19:02.766
Thousands.

19:02.808 --> 19:05.394
Now, please find out
if he's made any other offers

19:05.435 --> 19:06.895
anywhere near town.

19:06.937 --> 19:08.355
- Okay.

19:08.397 --> 19:11.358
[dramatic music]

19:11.400 --> 19:13.569
♪ ♪

19:13.610 --> 19:15.112
- [sighs]

19:15.154 --> 19:16.822
[knock at door]

19:16.864 --> 19:19.491
- Uh, Mayor Lang,
got a minute?

19:19.533 --> 19:21.410
- Uh, I'm kind of in the middle
of something, Chuck.

19:21.451 --> 19:22.786
What's this about?

19:22.828 --> 19:24.997
- Um...

19:25.038 --> 19:26.582
the Kents.

19:26.623 --> 19:30.711
♪ ♪

19:30.752 --> 19:32.629
- Jordan!
[whooshing]

19:34.548 --> 19:36.925
You confronted Lex Luthor
about your father's heart?

19:36.967 --> 19:38.260
- Dude, you told her?

19:38.302 --> 19:41.638
- Don't look at him.
Look at me.

19:41.680 --> 19:43.348
- I was trying to save Dad.

19:43.390 --> 19:45.309
- He knows it was you.

19:45.350 --> 19:46.685
- What?

19:46.727 --> 19:49.021
- Lex Luthor knows
who you are now.

19:49.062 --> 19:51.064
He knows
who your father is.

19:51.106 --> 19:52.649
- How?
- Because you gave him

19:52.691 --> 19:56.987
the pieces he needed
to put it together.

19:57.029 --> 19:59.406
- Whatever.
It doesn't matter anyway.

19:59.448 --> 20:01.033
- Are you out
of your damn mind?

20:01.074 --> 20:02.743
He could go
to "the Daily Planet,"

20:02.784 --> 20:04.578
do an interview,
post it online.

20:04.620 --> 20:06.496
- So what?

20:06.538 --> 20:08.624
- So everything this family
has done to protect our secret,

20:08.665 --> 20:11.710
to live like we have,
is over.

20:11.752 --> 20:13.462
- Who cares
about any of that?

20:13.503 --> 20:15.255
All that matters
is saving Dad.

20:15.297 --> 20:16.757
- That is not
what this is about.

20:16.798 --> 20:18.842
- Yes, it is.
You were the one that said

20:18.884 --> 20:20.427
that you couldn't sit around
doing nothing.

20:20.469 --> 20:22.262
Well, neither can I!

20:22.304 --> 20:24.640
- This is not a forest fire,
Jordan--this is Lex Luthor.

20:24.681 --> 20:26.433
- I can handle him.
- No, you can't.

20:26.475 --> 20:28.936
You're not ready yet.
You are not your father!

20:28.977 --> 20:32.856
♪ ♪

20:32.898 --> 20:34.983
Not yet, anyway.

20:35.025 --> 20:36.693
[cell phone vibrates]

20:36.735 --> 20:39.905
Hey, Lana,
can I call you back later?

20:39.947 --> 20:41.448
God.

20:41.490 --> 20:45.535
Yes.
Okay, I'll be right in.

20:45.577 --> 20:49.456
- Mom, I-I'm sorry
I-I didn't tell you.

20:49.498 --> 20:51.083
- We'll talk
about this later.

20:51.124 --> 20:53.460
Right now
I have to go see Lana.

20:53.502 --> 20:56.296
You and your brother
are to stay in your rooms

20:56.338 --> 21:00.759
and do just absolutely nothing
until I get back.

21:00.801 --> 21:02.678
Am I clear?

21:02.719 --> 21:04.680
- Yes, ma'am.

21:04.721 --> 21:11.687
♪ ♪

21:11.728 --> 21:13.772
[sighs]

21:17.192 --> 21:18.610
- I'll have the Reuben.

21:18.652 --> 21:20.529
Thousand Island
on the side, please.

21:20.570 --> 21:22.948
- Uh, chips or fries?
- Crinkle fries.

21:22.990 --> 21:25.075
[door bell jingles]

21:25.117 --> 21:26.368
- Copy that.

21:26.410 --> 21:29.371
[soft dramatic music]

21:29.413 --> 21:30.789
- You got a menu?

21:30.831 --> 21:32.082
- Next time,
wait to be seated.

21:32.124 --> 21:33.750
- You want me to move?

21:33.792 --> 21:37.337
♪ ♪

21:37.379 --> 21:40.465
- You're fine right there.

21:40.507 --> 21:43.552
- Ugh. Things just keep
getting worse.

21:43.593 --> 21:45.345
- It sounds like
Chuck's the only one

21:45.387 --> 21:48.724
who put two and two
together.

21:48.765 --> 21:52.060
- I didn't think anyone saw
Jordan fly off with Clark.

21:52.102 --> 21:54.688
- Uh, it's not that.

21:54.730 --> 21:57.232
Chuck lost his wife
a few years ago.

21:57.274 --> 22:00.777
And when he saw how you
and the boys were reacting,

22:00.819 --> 22:04.781
he just knew.

22:04.823 --> 22:07.242
- I guess I need to start
accepting the fact

22:07.284 --> 22:10.412
that the whole world is going
to know our secret soon.

22:10.454 --> 22:12.664
- Not necessarily.

22:12.706 --> 22:14.791
He promised
he wouldn't say anything.

22:14.833 --> 22:16.918
He said after everything
Superman has done,

22:16.960 --> 22:18.920
it's the least he could do.

22:18.962 --> 22:22.466
- Probably doesn't matter.
Luthor figured it out, too.

22:22.507 --> 22:24.426
- How?

22:24.468 --> 22:28.388
- Jordan.

22:28.430 --> 22:30.098
When he first got his powers,

22:30.140 --> 22:31.767
I thought
it would really help him

22:31.808 --> 22:35.562
work through a lot
of his emotional problems.

22:35.604 --> 22:39.691
But the more I see
why he uses them--

22:39.733 --> 22:43.653
to prove himself
and to get fame and attention--

22:43.695 --> 22:46.239
I'm starting to think
it was the worst thing

22:46.281 --> 22:49.743
that could have happened
to him.

22:49.785 --> 22:52.788
♪ ♪

22:52.829 --> 22:55.123
[knock at door]

22:55.165 --> 22:57.751
- You agree with her,
don't you?

22:57.793 --> 23:00.003
♪ ♪

23:00.045 --> 23:01.880
[sighs]

23:01.922 --> 23:03.757
- What are you
talking about?

23:03.799 --> 23:06.218
- You don't think
I'll ever be like dad.

23:06.259 --> 23:09.054
- I don't think anyone
will ever be like dad.

23:09.096 --> 23:13.225
- Especially
a guy like me.

23:13.266 --> 23:16.853
- [sighs]

23:16.895 --> 23:19.189
I think you need to stop
asking me questions like that.

23:19.231 --> 23:21.983
[heartbeat pounding]

23:22.025 --> 23:24.653
♪ ♪

23:24.694 --> 23:26.905
- I can hear it.

23:26.947 --> 23:29.574
- What?
- Dad's heart.

23:29.616 --> 23:31.910
- There's, like,
8 billion hearts in the world.

23:31.952 --> 23:33.537
How do you know
it's Dad's?

23:33.578 --> 23:37.249
- Human hearts beat twice.
Dad's beats three times.

23:37.290 --> 23:39.167
I can get it.
- No.

23:39.209 --> 23:40.669
Mom said
not to go anywhere.

23:40.710 --> 23:41.962
- I don't care.

23:42.003 --> 23:43.839
- Hold on.

23:43.880 --> 23:46.800
Luthor just found out
that you're Superman's son,

23:46.842 --> 23:49.094
and now you're hearing
Dad's heart?

23:49.136 --> 23:51.638
[scoffs]
This is obviously a trap.

23:51.680 --> 23:53.640
- Then he's making
a mistake.

23:53.682 --> 23:55.684
- Dude.
- Luthor doesn't think

23:55.725 --> 23:59.312
I'll do whatever it takes
to get it back...

23:59.354 --> 24:00.939
but he's wrong.

24:00.981 --> 24:05.318
♪ ♪

24:10.866 --> 24:12.200
- Hello?
- Luthor's here.

24:12.242 --> 24:14.035
- Where?
At the diner?

24:14.077 --> 24:15.871
- No, at my house.
Yes, at the diner.

24:15.912 --> 24:17.747
I'm always
at this stupid diner.

24:17.789 --> 24:19.416
And he's about to order,
so this might be your chance.

24:19.458 --> 24:21.084
If Luthor has your dad's heart,

24:21.126 --> 24:22.669
now might be
the time to get it.

24:22.711 --> 24:25.046
- You want me to what?
Break into his hotel?

24:25.088 --> 24:27.466
No, I can't just storm
into a trap like Jordan.

24:27.507 --> 24:29.134
- This is safe.
I promise.

24:29.176 --> 24:31.136
He's at the counter,
facing away from the hotel.

24:31.178 --> 24:33.763
I can stall him while you're
in there--he'll never know.

24:33.805 --> 24:35.265
I know what I said earlier,

24:35.307 --> 24:37.559
but what if this
is your last shot to get it?

24:37.601 --> 24:39.686
My mom did break in
his door earlier.

24:39.728 --> 24:41.521
Hurry up.
I'll keep him busy.

24:41.563 --> 24:44.065
- Sarah, wait.
[line beeps]

24:44.107 --> 24:47.068
[dramatic music]

24:47.110 --> 24:50.071
[whooshing]

24:50.113 --> 24:57.204
♪ ♪

25:08.298 --> 25:10.342
- So what can
I get for you?

25:10.383 --> 25:11.843
- How's the flank steak?

25:11.885 --> 25:14.804
- Better than prison food.

25:14.846 --> 25:16.389
- You'd be surprised.

25:16.431 --> 25:19.392
- Hmm.

25:19.434 --> 25:21.394
Well, you know, honestly,

25:21.436 --> 25:23.980
we're more well-known
for our off-the-menu stuff.

25:24.022 --> 25:25.732
- Is that so?

25:25.774 --> 25:27.984
- Yeah, we have
a killer porterhouse,

25:28.026 --> 25:29.319
if you like steak.

25:29.361 --> 25:31.238
It's seasoned
with butter, salt.

25:31.279 --> 25:34.074
Takes about 20 minutes,

25:34.115 --> 25:36.993
but I promise
it's worth the wait.

25:37.035 --> 25:40.038
- I'll take your word for it.

25:40.080 --> 25:47.170
♪ ♪

26:08.024 --> 26:09.568
I didn't order this.

26:09.609 --> 26:11.194
- Oh, it's on the house...

26:11.236 --> 26:12.988
you know, for the wait.

26:13.029 --> 26:16.366
Um, it's also the best tea
in, uh, Kansas.

26:16.408 --> 26:18.159
- Sarah.

26:18.201 --> 26:20.620
- Mom, hey.

26:20.662 --> 26:24.457
- Mayor Lang, Lex Luthor.

26:24.499 --> 26:25.875
- I know who you are.

26:25.917 --> 26:27.419
- Your daughter
was just pouring me

26:27.460 --> 26:30.088
some of this famous tea.

26:30.130 --> 26:33.383
- Hmm.
Lois Lane's favorite.

26:33.425 --> 26:35.594
- I'm going to be in town
for a while.

26:35.635 --> 26:37.762
There's some business matters
I'd like to discuss.

26:37.804 --> 26:39.222
- Just call my office.

26:39.264 --> 26:42.017
Everything goes
through my assistant.

26:42.058 --> 26:43.727
You--
- Hmm?

26:43.768 --> 26:46.271
- Come with me.

26:46.313 --> 26:53.320
♪ ♪

27:01.119 --> 27:03.371
[sizzling]

27:03.413 --> 27:06.082
Hey, Big Sugar,
can we have a minute?

27:10.086 --> 27:12.672
Why were you being nice
to that man?

27:12.714 --> 27:14.174
- It's my job to be nice.

27:14.215 --> 27:15.759
- You've never been
that nice to anyone

27:15.800 --> 27:17.218
in your whole life.

27:17.260 --> 27:18.720
And you saw what he did
to the Kents.

27:18.762 --> 27:21.056
- I just gave him a tea.

27:21.097 --> 27:22.641
- Sarah?
- Hmm?

27:22.682 --> 27:24.476
- I'm your mother.
I know you.

27:24.517 --> 27:26.353
I know you're up to something.

27:26.394 --> 27:28.855
- [sighs]

27:31.191 --> 27:34.069
[sighs]
Okay, um...

27:34.110 --> 27:36.363
I-I'm trying to keep him busy

27:36.404 --> 27:38.073
so that Jon can sneak
into his hotel room

27:38.114 --> 27:40.200
to try and find
his dad's heart.

27:40.241 --> 27:41.701
- What is wrong
with you?

27:41.743 --> 27:43.161
If they find the heart,

27:43.203 --> 27:44.788
they have a chance
at saving their dad.

27:44.829 --> 27:47.415
- Does Lois know?
- I'm not sure, honestly, but--

27:47.457 --> 27:49.250
What? You told me
to be there for Jon.

27:49.292 --> 27:51.169
- That is not what I meant,
and you know it.

27:51.211 --> 27:54.339
- Well...
this is Smallville.

27:54.381 --> 27:55.840
We look out
for each other.

27:55.882 --> 27:57.801
Mom, what was I supposed to do?

27:57.842 --> 28:00.970
- [sighs] Just text Jon
to get out of there.

28:01.012 --> 28:07.727
♪ ♪

28:07.769 --> 28:10.605
Where did he go?

28:10.647 --> 28:17.278
♪ ♪

29:04.284 --> 29:06.786
[heartbeat intensifies]

29:10.915 --> 29:14.753
- I've got dinner.

29:14.794 --> 29:17.005
Jordan?
Jonathan?

29:17.046 --> 29:20.133
[cell phone ringing, buzzing]

29:26.848 --> 29:28.308
Clark?

29:28.349 --> 29:30.310
- Lois...

29:30.351 --> 29:32.812
I'm so happy
to hear your voice.

29:32.854 --> 29:34.814
- Clark, I thought
you were dead.

29:34.856 --> 29:37.734
- I know.
I know.

29:37.776 --> 29:40.612
That's because I am dead...

29:40.653 --> 29:42.947
as dead as one of your boys
is about to be.

29:42.989 --> 29:48.286
♪ ♪

29:48.328 --> 29:51.414
[footsteps approaching]

30:00.799 --> 30:03.885
[thumping]

30:08.556 --> 30:10.308
- Got him!
He's over here!

30:10.350 --> 30:12.811
- I know this is you, Luthor.

30:12.852 --> 30:15.939
- The question is,
which son do you love more?

30:15.980 --> 30:17.857
- Your sons are in danger.

30:17.899 --> 30:20.610
If you want Jordan to live,
press one.

30:20.652 --> 30:22.612
- You leave my boys alone!

30:22.654 --> 30:24.656
- If you want Jonathan
to live, press two.

30:24.697 --> 30:26.241
This is a limited-time offer,

30:26.282 --> 30:28.159
so you'll have
to choose quickly.

30:28.201 --> 30:30.703
- Jordan, Jon, where are you?
- Your sons are in danger.

30:30.745 --> 30:32.914
[door creaking]

30:32.956 --> 30:37.752
♪ ♪

30:37.794 --> 30:40.171
- Jonathan, you need
to get home right now.

30:40.213 --> 30:43.341
Come on. Come on, hurry up.
- Okay.

30:52.767 --> 30:55.478
- [grunting]

31:02.026 --> 31:04.153
- Aah!

31:04.195 --> 31:11.119
♪ ♪

31:25.925 --> 31:29.387
[grunting]

31:35.977 --> 31:38.938
[dramatic music]

31:38.980 --> 31:45.528
♪ ♪

31:46.779 --> 31:49.490
[men grunting]

31:51.910 --> 31:54.579
- Where is Luthor?

31:54.621 --> 31:56.789
Where is he?

31:56.831 --> 32:00.877
♪ ♪

32:00.919 --> 32:04.130
[loud ringing]

32:06.633 --> 32:08.801
- If you want Jordan to live,
press one.

32:08.843 --> 32:11.179
If you want Jonathan
to live, press two.

32:11.220 --> 32:13.181
You have ten seconds
to choose.

32:13.222 --> 32:15.350
Stop this! Stop it!
- Nine...

32:15.391 --> 32:18.853
eight, seven, six...

32:18.895 --> 32:21.940
If you don't choose,
they'll both die.

32:21.981 --> 32:26.152
Three, two, one.

32:26.194 --> 32:30.198
[keypad beeps]
Thank you for participating.

32:30.239 --> 32:32.200
- [exhales sharply]

32:32.241 --> 32:35.203
[somber music]

32:35.244 --> 32:41.626
♪ ♪

32:41.668 --> 32:45.129
[door clicks]

32:45.171 --> 32:47.215
- Mom?
- Where's your brother?

32:47.256 --> 32:49.467
Where is your brother?

32:49.509 --> 32:52.595
[loud ringing continues]

32:52.637 --> 32:57.016
♪ ♪

32:57.058 --> 32:59.811
- [groaning]

32:59.852 --> 33:02.563
[ringing stops]

33:02.605 --> 33:04.524
- I told you
you weren't ready.

33:04.565 --> 33:08.194
And here you are
on the same day.

33:08.236 --> 33:10.530
- I'm not leaving
without his heart.

33:10.571 --> 33:13.241
- Who says
you're leaving at all?

33:13.282 --> 33:16.119
[loud ringing resumes]
- [groaning]

33:16.160 --> 33:21.207
♪ ♪

33:21.249 --> 33:22.917
[ringing stops]

33:22.959 --> 33:25.003
[breathing heavily]

33:25.044 --> 33:30.008
Give...me...his...heart.

33:30.049 --> 33:31.884
- You want his heart?

33:31.926 --> 33:35.722
- [groaning]

33:35.763 --> 33:42.854
♪ ♪

33:46.441 --> 33:48.151
- Here.

33:48.192 --> 33:54.657
♪ ♪

33:54.699 --> 33:56.409
- [grunts,
breathing heavily]

33:59.495 --> 34:03.708
- I could kill you
right now...

34:03.750 --> 34:05.918
Take you away
from your mother forever.

34:05.960 --> 34:08.629
- [whimpering]

34:08.671 --> 34:10.631
- But I won't.

34:10.673 --> 34:13.009
- [grunts,
breathing heavily]

34:13.051 --> 34:19.057
♪ ♪

34:19.098 --> 34:22.852
- But I do have
to take something.

34:22.894 --> 34:25.480
- No!

34:25.521 --> 34:29.233
[sobbing]
No!

34:29.275 --> 34:31.110
No!

34:31.152 --> 34:33.571
No!

34:33.613 --> 34:36.949
No!

34:36.991 --> 34:38.576
No!

34:40.453 --> 34:43.039
[cell phone buzzing]

34:43.081 --> 34:44.957
- Is it Jordan?

34:44.999 --> 34:49.003
- Someone tripped the alarm
at the "Gazette."

34:49.045 --> 34:51.756
[engine revving,
tires squealing]

34:56.969 --> 35:04.018
♪ ♪

35:04.560 --> 35:07.897
[door creaking]

35:10.608 --> 35:13.903
- [crying]

35:17.156 --> 35:20.701
[somber music]

35:20.743 --> 35:24.122
You were right.

35:24.163 --> 35:28.626
I wasn't ready.

35:28.668 --> 35:30.878
Luthor destroyed
Dad's heart.

35:30.920 --> 35:33.798
♪ ♪

35:33.840 --> 35:36.717
And now we can never
get him back.

35:36.759 --> 35:39.637
♪ ♪

35:39.679 --> 35:42.557
[crying softly]

35:42.598 --> 35:44.892
[sobbing]

35:44.934 --> 35:47.520
I'm sorry.

35:47.562 --> 35:50.273
♪ ♪

35:50.314 --> 35:53.025
I'm so sorry.

36:01.742 --> 36:04.287
- I never
should have gone there.

36:04.328 --> 36:07.665
- This isn't your fault.

36:07.707 --> 36:10.126
- I told you
it was a trap.

36:10.168 --> 36:12.211
- Jon, none of this
is on your brother.

36:12.253 --> 36:14.714
- We had one chance,
and he just wouldn't listen!

36:14.755 --> 36:16.424
- Stop.

36:16.465 --> 36:18.801
The only person to blame
is Lex Luthor.

36:18.843 --> 36:21.095
And this is exactly
what he wants--

36:21.137 --> 36:23.556
for us to turn on
each other.

36:23.598 --> 36:26.309
- But he's right.

36:26.350 --> 36:28.477
Dad's dead.

36:28.519 --> 36:30.980
[somber music]

36:31.022 --> 36:34.817
It's my fault.

36:34.859 --> 36:38.029
- No.

36:38.070 --> 36:41.616
You held on to hope...

36:41.657 --> 36:44.660
just like
he would have wanted.

36:44.702 --> 36:48.873
♪ ♪

36:48.915 --> 36:51.459
You both did.

36:51.500 --> 36:53.336
- [scoffs]

36:53.377 --> 36:55.963
I just...

36:56.005 --> 36:57.965
never thought he'd die.

36:58.007 --> 37:05.097
♪ ♪

37:05.890 --> 37:08.226
I mean...

37:08.267 --> 37:11.646
he's...

37:11.687 --> 37:15.399
He was...
- Superman.

37:15.441 --> 37:22.406
♪ ♪

37:22.448 --> 37:24.617
- What are we supposed
to do now...

37:24.659 --> 37:27.662
♪ ♪

37:27.703 --> 37:32.166
Without Dad?

37:32.208 --> 37:35.044
- I don't--I don't know.

37:35.086 --> 37:39.840
♪ ♪

37:39.882 --> 37:43.719
I don't know.

37:46.097 --> 37:50.184
But I think it's time
that we go say goodbye.

37:50.226 --> 37:56.691
♪ ♪

37:56.732 --> 37:58.484
- Everything okay?

37:58.526 --> 38:00.987
- You find
something promising?

38:01.028 --> 38:03.239
- The Manning farm--
40 acres on the edge of town.

38:03.281 --> 38:07.326
it would be ideal
for a new headquarters.

38:07.368 --> 38:09.453
- Then make an offer.

38:09.495 --> 38:12.873
- I already did.

38:12.915 --> 38:15.459
Regarding Elizabeth...

38:15.501 --> 38:17.461
Lane knew more
than he was letting on.

38:17.503 --> 38:18.963
- Meaning?

38:19.005 --> 38:21.674
- We flipped someone
at the DOD.

38:21.716 --> 38:23.551
Turns out Elizabeth
made contact

38:23.592 --> 38:26.846
right before
you got out.

38:26.887 --> 38:29.557
- Why would she do that?

38:29.598 --> 38:32.435
- She was hoping
not to be found.

38:32.476 --> 38:35.021
- [sighs]

38:37.648 --> 38:42.111
Her mother has been poisoning
the well for 17 years.

38:42.153 --> 38:45.156
It'll take time.

38:45.197 --> 38:47.533
Where is Elizabeth now?

38:47.575 --> 38:51.579
- Seems the only person
who knows that is Sam Lane.

38:51.620 --> 38:55.291
[dramatic music]

38:55.333 --> 38:58.336
- Mom, are you serious?
You're going to block his deal?

38:58.377 --> 39:00.379
- Well, I'm not going to let
Lex Luthor set up shop

39:00.421 --> 39:02.298
in Smallville.
- Really?

39:02.340 --> 39:04.300
We're standing up to him.

39:04.342 --> 39:06.177
- No, I'm standing up to him.
- Mom.

39:06.218 --> 39:08.721
- Sarah, I don't know how
he's going to retaliate,

39:08.763 --> 39:12.767
but when he does, he has
to direct it at me and just me.

39:12.808 --> 39:17.021
[cell phone buzzes]
Okay?

39:17.063 --> 39:20.024
[somber music]

39:20.066 --> 39:23.027
♪ ♪

39:23.069 --> 39:25.196
What is it?

39:25.237 --> 39:28.157
- They couldn't get
the heart.

39:28.199 --> 39:30.743
I'm so sorry, Mom.
Mr. Kent's dead.

39:30.785 --> 39:32.620
- What?

39:32.661 --> 39:34.830
♪ ♪

39:34.872 --> 39:37.708
Oh, but...

39:37.750 --> 39:39.502
I've known...

39:39.543 --> 39:43.672
Clark my whole life,
ever since we were kids.

39:43.714 --> 39:46.759
[crying softly]

39:46.801 --> 39:53.891
♪ ♪

40:09.073 --> 40:12.618
- Lois...

40:12.660 --> 40:15.704
He left something
for all of you.

40:15.746 --> 40:22.837
♪ ♪

40:24.547 --> 40:26.006
- It's Dad.

40:26.048 --> 40:28.092
- Dad?

40:28.134 --> 40:29.969
- Clark.

40:30.010 --> 40:32.972
- Lois, boys.

40:33.013 --> 40:35.683
- When did you do this?

40:35.724 --> 40:38.811
- Right after we built
this place.

40:38.853 --> 40:42.148
I was going to tell you sooner,
but you got sick.

40:42.189 --> 40:45.401
♪ ♪

40:45.443 --> 40:48.696
- [crying] It's hard
seeing you like this.

40:48.737 --> 40:51.157
- I was really hoping
you'd never have to.

40:51.198 --> 40:54.493
♪ ♪

40:54.535 --> 40:56.787
I'm sorry if I let you down.

40:56.829 --> 40:59.790
- [exhales sharply]
Clark, you never let me down,

40:59.832 --> 41:02.918
not once.

41:02.960 --> 41:06.505
I just...
[sighs]

41:06.547 --> 41:09.091
I just wasn't ready
to lose you.

41:09.133 --> 41:13.721
- Yeah, me either.

41:13.762 --> 41:16.140
- So this is it?

41:16.182 --> 41:17.975
This is all
we have left of you?

41:18.017 --> 41:21.145
♪ ♪

41:21.187 --> 41:24.607
- I'll always be here
at the Fortress to help...

41:24.648 --> 41:27.443
however I can.
- [sobs]

41:27.485 --> 41:31.906
- But out there...

41:31.947 --> 41:34.283
it's just going to have to be
the three of you.

41:34.325 --> 41:40.998
♪ ♪

41:41.040 --> 41:44.001
- [cries]

41:44.043 --> 41:51.133
♪ ♪

42:16.992 --> 42:19.036
- Greg, move your head.
